# 05-Email: EmailJS as Single Email Service

This project uses **EmailJS** for all email sending, client-side only. Do not introduce Nodemailer, SendGrid, Resend, or other email providers.

## Client-Side (Browser)
- **Package**: `@emailjs/browser`
- **Contact form**: `client/src/components/Footer/hooks/useEmailSend.tsx`
- **Calculator lead notification**: `client/src/utils/calculatorLeadEmail.ts` (fire-and-forget after API success)
- **Env vars**: `VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID`, `VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID`, `VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY`, `VITE_EMAILJS_CALCULATOR_TEMPLATE_ID` (optional)

## When Adding New Email Flows
1. Create an EmailJS template in the dashboard.
2. Use `@emailjs/browser` from the client (same pattern as contact form and calculator lead).
3. Never add server-side email (Nodemailer, @emailjs/nodejs, SMTP, etc.).
